benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/cache/accounts/{accountId} - Invalidates Caches per account level

covered: DELETE - Valid Deletion: Successful 204 with empty body for valid accountId (TC01, TC09, TC17, TC19).
DELETE - Non-Existent Resource: 404 when account not found (TC02, TC16, TC18).
Input Validation: 400 for invalid/malformed accountId formats incl. short strings, SQLi, XSS (TC03, TC12, TC14, TC15).
Authorization: 401 for unauthenticated or invalid/expired token (TC05, TC06).
Operational Resilience: 503 when cache service unavailable or system degraded (TC07, TC08).
Concurrency/Load: Concurrent DELETE requests succeed with acceptable performance (TC13).
Path Handling: Missing path segment returns 404 (TC04).
gaps: DELETE - Concurrency race condition: No scenario where the target resource state changes mid-operation (e.g., concurrent invalidation causing conflicting outcomes).
Soft Deletes: Not addressed; if not applicable for cache invalidation, note explicitly to avoid ambiguity.
Content negotiation/headers: Story says produces application/json; tests don’t verify Content-Type/Accept behavior for errors and do not confirm absence/presence of headers for 204.
Idempotency: No scenario verifying repeated DELETEs on the same account are consistently 204 and side-effect free.
Rate limiting/throttling: No test for 429 or behavior under burst traffic beyond performance timing.
Audit/observability: No checks for admin action logging or correlation IDs (if standard in platform).
Negative method matrix: Only GET tested for 405; no tests for POST/PUT/PATCH/HEAD/OPTIONS behavior on this endpoint.
Boundary validation of UUID: No explicit tests for valid UUID edge variants (uppercase, with/without braces, version-specific) against the documented pattern.
recommendations: Add a race-condition test: fire concurrent DELETEs for the same account and assert consistent 204 responses and no error/leakage.
Clarify and document soft-delete applicability for cache invalidation; if N/A, state it in the story and mark as not applicable.
Verify headers: assert Content-Type application/json on error responses; assert no Content-Type for 204 or explicitly defined behavior; include Accept header negotiation tests.
Add idempotency test: repeat DELETE for the same account multiple times and confirm stable 204 and correct system state.
Add rate limiting tests: burst DELETEs to check for 429 or defined behavior under throttling.
Extend method matrix: ensure POST/PUT/PATCH/HEAD/OPTIONS return 405 (or appropriate) with standard error payload.
Expand UUID boundary tests: valid UUID cases (uppercase, different versions) that should pass per pattern, and near-miss invalids that should fail.
If applicable, add an internal error path (500) simulation for unexpected failures distinct from external cache service 503, and validate error contract.
